==Finnish==
===Noun===

'''hitto''' (plural ''hitot'')

''(mild expletive)'' Hell, fuck, heck, or shit. Somewhat comparable to Geezers!

Finnish synonyms: [[helvetti]], [[halvattu]], [[hiisi]], [[piru]]

===Usage notes===

''Hitto'' is never used in illative case in an imperative sentence, unlike [[helvetti]] or [[vittu]]. Doing that would sound lame. Therefore, you can say ''mene helvettiin'' or ''painu vittuun'' to tell someone to get lost, but you can't say ''mene hittoon''. However, you can ask in the illative case ''Mihin hittoon se tyyppi meni?'' (Where the hell did that guy go?) or in the elative case ''Mistä hitosta sä ton löysit?'' (Where the hell did you find that?). Generally you can apply the usage examples of ''[[halvattu]]''.

===Etymology===

Probably, but not necessarily, derived from Swedish ''hitåt'' which sounds like "Out of here!"

